notes: Kabul’s primary school admissions do not use any centralized choice or matching system. Enrollment is handled locally: families register children directly at nearby public schools or opt for private schools, with access largely determined by location and available capacity ([euaa.europa.eu](https://euaa.europa.eu/country-guidance-afghanistan-2022/2135-education-children-and-girls-particular#:~:text=In%20general%2C%20in%20the%20cities,COI%20query%20on%20education%20sector)). Education is compulsory through lower secondary, and schooling (public, private, or madrasa) is generally open to all eligible children without a citywide algorithm or ranked application process ([euaa.europa.eu](https://euaa.europa.eu/country-guidance-afghanistan-2022/2135-education-children-and-girls-particular#:~:text=madrasas%2C%20has%20been%20compulsory%20in,rates%2C%20particularly%20for%20girls%2C%20were)). Afghanistan’s legal framework guarantees free basic education as a right, implying no competitive selection mechanism at the primary level ([www.wipo.int](https://www.wipo.int/wipolex/ar/text/489954#:~:text=Education%20is%20the%20right%20of,of%20charge%20by%20the%20state)). Thus, Kabul’s primary education admissions are best characterized as uncoordinated, with no coordinated choice and assignment system in place.

Kabul’s secondary education admissions do not use a centralized choice system. Students do not submit ranked school preferences, and there is no citywide algorithm assigning school seats. Enrollment is handled by individual schools or local education offices, with students generally attending a nearby school if capacity allows ([studylib.net](https://studylib.net/doc/5871589/fair-access-of-children-to-education-in-afghanistan#:~:text=In%20its%20third%20report%20on,There%20are%20fewer)). Both public and private secondary schools operate in Kabul ([moe.gov.af](https://moe.gov.af/index.php/en/supervision-honorable-minister-education-over-standardized-examinations-10thdistrict-kabul-city#:~:text=subjects%20of%20Islamic%20Education%2C%20Language%2C,30%20locations%20in%20Kabul%20City)), but neither sector uses a unified assignment algorithm. Admission largely depends on local availability rather than formal priority criteria ([studylib.net](https://studylib.net/doc/5871589/fair-access-of-children-to-education-in-afghanistan#:~:text=provincial%20capitals,number%20of%20schools%20in%20the)). Afghan law guarantees free education for all citizens through secondary level, emphasizing open access ([www.wipo.int](https://www.wipo.int/wipolex/ar/text/489954#:~:text=Education%20is%20the%20right%20of,of%20charge%20by%20the%20state)). In practice, limited school capacity and distance to schools are major factors affecting enrollment ([studylib.net](https://studylib.net/doc/5871589/fair-access-of-children-to-education-in-afghanistan#:~:text=provincial%20capitals,number%20of%20schools%20in%20the)). Since 2021, the Taliban authorities have barred girls from attending secondary school, a blanket restriction outside any assignment process ([8am.media](https://8am.media/eng/talibans-exclusive-national-entrance-examination/#:~:text=position,also%20barred%20from%20attending%20school)). No coordinated choice and assignment system has been adopted in Kabul, so there are no specific adoption or reform dates.

([www.afghanistan-analysts.org](https://www.afghanistan-analysts.org/en/reports/economy-development-environment/battleground-kankur-afghan-students-difficult-way-into-higher-education/#:~:text=points%20needed%20to%20qualify%20for,science%2C%20engineering%2C%20law%2C%20political%20science)) Kabul’s tertiary admissions are managed through Afghanistan’s national Kankor exam, a centralized system meeting all CCAS criteria. High school graduates submit a ranked list of up to five preferred university programs, and a single computerized algorithm operated by the National Examination Authority assigns each student to at most one public university based on their exam score ([www.researchgate.net](https://www.researchgate.net/publication/394407024_A_STUDY_OF_KANKOR_PROCESS_MAPPING_IN_AFGHANISTAN#:~:text=online%20website%20of%20the%20Kankor,to%20public%20sector%20universities%20is)). Private universities generally conduct separate entrance tests, so the coordinated process primarily applies to public institutions ([www.universityworldnews.com](https://www.universityworldnews.com/post.php?story=20221007134432857#:~:text=Locally%20known%20as%20%E2%80%98Kankor%E2%80%99%2C%20the,Kabul%20will)). This system was introduced in 1960 ([nexa.gov.af](https://nexa.gov.af/en/about_us#:~:text=Since%201960%2C%20the%20Kankor%20examination,scientific%2C%20specialized%2C%20and%20inclusive%20exams)) and later reformed for transparency, culminating in an independent exam authority (NEXA) in 2018 ([nexa.gov.af](https://nexa.gov.af/en/about_us#:~:text=underwent%20quantitative%20and%20qualitative%20development,established%20as%20an%20independent%20authority)). Under Taliban rule since 2021, the Kankor exam continues for male students, but female candidates have been barred from participation since early 2023 ([theafghantimes.com](https://theafghantimes.com/education/2024/07/06/university-entrance-exam-in-afghanistan-a-significant-decrease-in-participants/#:~:text=Exclusion%20of%20females%20from%20Kankoor,exams%20on%20January%2021%2C%202023)), leading to a sharp decline in exam takers. Despite these challenges, the fundamental mechanism remains a merit-based matching of students to available university seats using exam scores as the primary criterion.

Luanda does not use a centralized school choice or algorithmic assignment system for primary admissions. Instead, families must enroll children at individual schools (usually their local public school) rather than submitting a ranked list of preferred schools ([www.novojornal.co.ao](https://www.novojornal.co.ao/sociedade/detalhe/ano-lectivo-20252026-aulas-arrancaram-de-forma-timida-e-a-maioria-das-escolas-publicas-ainda-esta-a-ultimar-a-fase-de-matriculas-67132.html#:~:text=Na%20maioria%20das%20escolas%20da,ultimam%20a%20fase%20de%20matr%C3%ADculas)) ([jornalf8.net](https://jornalf8.net/2018/escolas-vao-ter-tudo-conseguirem-ter/#:~:text=Recorde,de%20alunos%20do%20ensino%20p%C3%BAblico)). There is no city-wide algorithm or single-offer process; each school manages its own intake and posts its own list of admitted students ([www.novojornal.co.ao](https://www.novojornal.co.ao/sociedade/detalhe/ano-lectivo-20252026-aulas-arrancaram-de-forma-timida-e-a-maioria-das-escolas-publicas-ainda-esta-a-ultimar-a-fase-de-matriculas-67132.html#:~:text=Na%20maioria%20das%20escolas%20da,ultimam%20a%20fase%20de%20matr%C3%ADculas)). Capacity shortfalls make enrollment competitive – many parents queue up and even resort to unofficial payments or in-kind contributions (such as cleaning supplies) to secure a spot for their child ([jornalf8.net](https://jornalf8.net/2018/escolas-vao-ter-tudo-conseguirem-ter/#:~:text=Recorde,de%20alunos%20do%20ensino%20p%C3%BAblico)) ([kietoeconomia.ao](https://kietoeconomia.ao/escolas-publicas-sem-dinheiro-obrigam-pais-a-darem-materiais-de-hiegiene-por-matricula#:~:text=Institui%C3%A7%C3%B5es%20do%20ensino%20prim%C3%A1ria%20na,e%20da%20confirma%C3%A7%C3%A3o%20de%20matr%C3%ADculas)). Thus, no Coordinated Choice and Assignment System exists for Luanda’s primary schools.

Luanda does not use a centralized school choice algorithm for secondary education. Instead, each public secondary school conducts its own admissions during an enrollment period, posting lists of accepted students individually ([novojornal.co.ao](https://novojornal.co.ao/sociedade/detalhe/ano-lectivo-20252026-aulas-arrancaram-de-forma-timida-e-a-maioria-das-escolas-publicas-ainda-esta-a-ultimar-a-fase-de-matriculas-67132.html#:~:text=Apesar%20de%20estar%20oficialmente%20aberto,matr%C3%ADculas%2C%20apurou%20o%20Novo%20Jornal)). There is no citywide platform where students rank multiple schools, and applicants must apply directly to their school(s) of interest. Selection is generally based on academic performance – for example, schools give priority to students with the highest grade averages in core subjects ([angoemprego.com](https://angoemprego.com/processo-de-inscricoes-nas-escolas-do-ii-ciclo-em-luanda-terminam-na-proxima-segunda-feira/#:~:text=Sobre%20o%20crit%C3%A9rio%20de%20selec%C3%A7%C3%A3o,Portuguesa%2C%20Matem%C3%A1tica%2C%20F%C3%ADsica%20e%20Qu%C3%ADmica)). Private and semi-public schools also manage admissions independently, without any coordinated system. A 2021 presidential decree simplified enrollment procedures (e.g., removing the need for official confirmation of school placements) ([simplifica.gov.ao](https://simplifica.gov.ao/ler-noticia/executivo-valida-certificados-emitidos-no-ensino-geral-e-elimina-obrigacao-de-confirmacao-de-matriculas#:~:text=A%20medida%20foi%20institucionalizada%20pelo,e%20ao%20ensino%20secund%C3%A1rio%20geral)), but it did not introduce a coordinated choice and assignment system. As a result, Luanda’s secondary school admissions remain decentralized and uncoordinated.

Luanda, like the rest of Angola, does not have a city-wide coordinated tertiary admission system. Instead, each higher education institution manages its own entrance examinations and selects students independently ([lex.ao](https://lex.ao/docs/presidente-da-republica/2019/decreto-presidencial-n-o-5-19-de-08-de-janeiro/#:~:text=7,definidas%20para%20os%20demais%20candidatos)). Applicants can apply to multiple universities and may choose more than one course at a single institution (e.g., Agostinho Neto University allows up to two course options per candidate) ([www.uan.ao](https://www.uan.ao/detalhes/noticia/inscricoes-para-os-exames-de-acesso-2023#:~:text=aplicativo%20Multicaixa%20Express%20para%20a,10000%2C00%20AOA%20por%20duas%20op%C3%A7%C3%B5es)). Admissions are based primarily on academic performance in institution-specific entrance exams ([lex.ao](https://lex.ao/docs/presidente-da-republica/2019/decreto-presidencial-n-o-5-19-de-08-de-janeiro/#:~:text=1,refer%C3%AAncia%20a%20nota%20m%C3%ADnima%20exigida)). The Ministry of Higher Education sets annual enrollment quotas (vagas) for each institution and oversees the process via a national commission (CNAES) ([mescti.gov.ao](https://mescti.gov.ao/web/noticias/vagas-para-o-ano-acad%C3%A9mico-20222023#:~:text=Cabe%20ao%20Minist%C3%A9rio%20do%20Ensino,dom%C3%ADnio%20e%20a%20preocupa%C3%A7%C3%A3o%20de)) ([lex.ao](https://lex.ao/docs/presidente-da-republica/2019/decreto-presidencial-n-o-5-19-de-08-de-janeiro/#:~:text=1,Institui%C3%A7%C3%B5es%20de%20Ensino%20Superior%2C%20no)). All public and private institutions must follow the national regulations, including reserving a small percentage of seats for special categories such as war veterans and persons with disabilities ([lex.ao](https://lex.ao/docs/presidente-da-republica/2019/decreto-presidencial-n-o-5-19-de-08-de-janeiro/#:~:text=Artigo%2020,%E2%80%8B)). Because there is no centralized algorithm providing a single offer to each student, the tertiary education admissions system in Luanda is classified as uncoordinated.

Abu Dhabi’s primary school admissions are not centrally coordinated. Private school admissions are handled by individual schools: parents apply directly to each preferred school, and if an offer is made, the school then facilitates the student’s registration with the education authority ([www.few.ae](https://www.few.ae/how-to-register-children-for-schools-in-abu-dhabi/#:~:text=Parents%20usually%20begin%20by%20applying,for%20the%20following%20academic%20year)). Public school placements for Emirati nationals are managed through the Ministry of Education’s online portal during set registration periods ([www.few.ae](https://www.few.ae/how-to-register-children-for-schools-in-abu-dhabi/#:~:text=Parents%20usually%20begin%20by%20applying,for%20the%20following%20academic%20year)). There is no unified application where families rank multiple schools, and no central algorithm for matching students to schools. Each school sets its own admission criteria – many private institutions require entrance exams or assessments as part of admissions ([www.constellationeducation.ae](https://www.constellationeducation.ae/post/uae-schools-admission-guide-smart-choices-for-relocating-families#:~:text=school,advance%20can%20improve%20admission%20prospects)), and some oversubscribed schools employ lotteries for entry-level grades ([adisuae.com](https://adisuae.com/admission/#:~:text=,Details%20of)). ADEK, the emirate’s education regulator, has introduced policies (such as banning pre-admission interviews for kindergarten applicants) to promote fairness ([www.thenationalnews.com](https://www.thenationalnews.com/uae/education/abu-dhabi-bans-private-schools-from-holding-pre-admission-interviews-for-nursery-children-1.317292#:~:text=ABU%20DHABI%20%2F%2F%20Education%20chiefs,the%20interviews%20were%20unscientific%20and)), but there is still no citywide matching mechanism. Consequently, students do not receive a single centrally allocated offer, and the conditions for a Coordinated Choice and Assignment System are not met ([www.constellationeducation.ae](https://www.constellationeducation.ae/post/uae-schools-admission-guide-smart-choices-for-relocating-families#:~:text=The%20process%20of%20getting%20into,prepared%20by%20your%20child%E2%80%99s%20previous)).

Abu Dhabi does not use a centralized choice and matching algorithm for secondary school admissions. Instead, each school or network manages its own intake. Public secondary schools assign students largely by residential catchment – Abu Dhabi even launched a service to automatically reserve a seat at a local public school for each newborn Emirati child based on the family’s home address ([www.khaleejtimes.com](https://www.khaleejtimes.com/uae/you-can-now-get-your-newborns-registered-for-school-in-uae#:~:text=Through%20ADSSSA%27s%20TAMM%20system%2C%20a,to%20confirm%20the%20school%20registration)). This means placements are determined by location rather than by parental ranked preferences. Similarly, charter and private schools in Abu Dhabi conduct their admissions independently. Families apply directly to individual schools and receive offers if the student meets that school’s requirements and seats are available ([www.dxbnewsnetwork.com](https://www.dxbnewsnetwork.com/abu-dhabi-charter-school-admission-guide#:~:text=3,submitted%20along%20with%20the%20application)). The Department of Education and Knowledge (ADEK) sets general admission guidelines for fairness (for example, schools cannot use entrance tests to selectively reject young applicants) ([gulfnews.com](https://gulfnews.com/living-in-uae/education/uae-what-are-the-requirements-for-admission-in-abu-dhabi-private-schools-six-details-parents-should-know-1.1705415286634#:~:text=4,support%20and%20not%20for%20the)), but there is no citywide Coordinated Choice and Assignment System. As of the latest information, no unified algorithm or single-offer placement system has been adopted for secondary education in Abu Dhabi ([www.khaleejtimes.com](https://www.khaleejtimes.com/uae/you-can-now-get-your-newborns-registered-for-school-in-uae#:~:text=At%20the%20moment%2C%20only%20public,service%20to%20include%20all%20schools)).

priority_criteria_source: University admission requires meeting academic benchmarks (grades and standardized exams) ([ae.ok.com](https://ae.ok.com/content/en/blog/admissions-and-registration-office-in-the-uae-361480909481971712/#:~:text=To%20register%20on%20NAPO%20UAE,Exam%20in%20the%20following%20subjects)) and aligning the chosen major with the student’s high school track ([ae.ok.com](https://ae.ok.com/content/en/blog/admissions-and-registration-office-in-the-uae-361480909481971712/#:~:text=,Attach%20all%20required%20documents)).
assignment_mechanism_source: No specific algorithm is publicly cited; officials note that students receive one offer through the centralized system, and those without offers are matched to programs ([www.khaleejtimes.com](https://www.khaleejtimes.com/uae/education/uae-new-system-provides-easier-access-to-higher-education-says-minister#:~:text=The%20new%20process%20takes%20into,rejected%20from%20a%20desired%20programme)).
adoption_year_source: NAPO has coordinated public university admissions for Emirati students since at least 2010 ([www.mohesr.gov.ae](https://www.mohesr.gov.ae/En/MediaCenter/archive/mohesr/news/Pages/Program_Secondary_Students2010.aspx#:~:text=Ministry%20of%20Higher%20Education%20and,students%20of%20applied%20technology%20institutes)), but the exact initial implementation year is not publicly documented.
reform_year_source: Major reforms ("NAPO 2.0") were rolled out in 2024 to make admissions more flexible ([www.khaleejtimes.com](https://www.khaleejtimes.com/uae/education/uae-new-system-provides-easier-access-to-higher-education-says-minister#:~:text=The%20new%20system%20rolled%20out,to%20finish%20their%20higher%20education)).
notes: Tertiary admissions in Abu Dhabi are centrally managed for UAE nationals via the National Admissions & Placement Office (NAPO). Emirati students submit a single application listing preferred universities/programmes ([ae.ok.com](https://ae.ok.com/content/en/blog/admissions-and-registration-office-in-the-uae-361480909481971712/#:~:text=Image%20The%20NAPO%20UAE%20platform,and%20children%20of%20Emirati%20nationals)) (historically up to five choices ([ae.ok.com](https://ae.ok.com/content/en/blog/admissions-and-registration-office-in-the-uae-361480909481971712/#:~:text=care%2C%20or%20status%20as%20a,Attach%20all%20required%20documents)); now no fixed limit ([www.mohesr.gov.ae](https://www.mohesr.gov.ae/En/EServices/ServiceCard/Napo/Pages/details-related-to-students-who-graduated-from-high-school-2023-2024.aspx#:~:text=,Maximum%20Institution%20Selection%20Limit%3A%20Unlimited))). Placement is primarily based on academic criteria such as high school grades and standardized test scores (e.g. EmSAT) ([ae.ok.com](https://ae.ok.com/content/en/blog/admissions-and-registration-office-in-the-uae-361480909481971712/#:~:text=To%20register%20on%20NAPO%20UAE,Exam%20in%20the%20following%20subjects)), and applicants must select majors aligned with their secondary school track ([ae.ok.com](https://ae.ok.com/content/en/blog/admissions-and-registration-office-in-the-uae-361480909481971712/#:~:text=,Attach%20all%20required%20documents)). A matching process then assigns each student one offer at a participating public institution ([www.mohesr.gov.ae](https://www.mohesr.gov.ae/En/MediaCenter/archive/mohesr/news/Pages/Higher-education-announces-the-start-of-registration-for-admission-to-government-institutions-of-higher-education.aspx#:~:text=education%20for%20the%20second%20semester,Emirates%20College%20for%20advanced%20education)). In 2024, the UAE introduced "NAPO 2.0", giving universities more autonomy in setting admission criteria and timelines ([www.khaleejtimes.com](https://www.khaleejtimes.com/uae/education/uae-new-system-provides-easier-access-to-higher-education-says-minister#:~:text=Schools%20will%20provide%20students%20guidance,are%20still%20in%20grade%2011)) and adding measures (like bridging courses) to ensure no student is left without a placement ([www.khaleejtimes.com](https://www.khaleejtimes.com/uae/education/uae-new-system-provides-easier-access-to-higher-education-says-minister#:~:text=The%20new%20process%20takes%20into,rejected%20from%20a%20desired%20programme)). This coordinated system applies to public institutions and UAE national students (including eligible residents); other students and certain universities (e.g. Khalifa University) follow independent admission processes ([ae.ok.com](https://ae.ok.com/content/en/blog/admissions-and-registration-office-in-the-uae-361480909481971712/#:~:text=The%20Admission%20and%20Registration%20Department,each%20institution%E2%80%99s%20individual%20admission%20criteria)) ([mohesr.gov.ae](https://mohesr.gov.ae/En/EServices/ServiceCard/NAPO/Pages/Details-related-to-students-who-graduated-from-high-school-2023-2024.aspx#:~:text=%E2%80%8BImportant%20Note%3A%20Students%20who%20wish,register%20directly%20with%20the%20institution)).

Dubai’s primary school admissions are managed on a per-school basis rather than through a centralized system. The majority of students attend one of Dubai’s 227 private schools ([www.education-uae.com](https://www.education-uae.com/dubai-school-waiting-lists-2025-trends-insights/#:~:text=Authority%20%28KHDA%29%20reported%20a%2012,new%20private%20schools%20by%202033)), and parents must apply to individual schools, often far in advance, as many popular schools maintain waiting lists ([www.thenationalnews.com](https://www.thenationalnews.com/uae/education/2023/07/07/enrol-child-school-dubai-abu-dhabi/#:~:text=Parents%20who%20want%20their%20child,open%20on%20about%20March%201)). The Knowledge and Human Development Authority (KHDA) provides an online directory and school ratings to help families choose, but it does not run a unified application or matching platform ([web.khda.gov.ae](https://web.khda.gov.ae/en/Guides/Parents/Enrolling-in-a-School#:~:text=To%20help%20you%20choose%20from,phone%20and%20do%20the%20same)). Each school sets its own admission criteria (e.g., first-come registration or entrance assessments for selective schools) and extends offers directly to parents ([www.thenationalnews.com](https://www.thenationalnews.com/uae/education/2023/07/07/enrol-child-school-dubai-abu-dhabi/#:~:text=Tests%20depend%20on%20the%20grade,fee%20of%20up%20to%20Dh1%2C000)). Government-run public schools (primarily for UAE citizens) have a centralized registration window via the Ministry of Education, but placements are determined by eligibility and local availability rather than a city-wide algorithm ([www.moe.gov.ae](https://www.moe.gov.ae/En/MediaCenter/News/Pages/Registration-for-the-2025-2026-academic-year-in-public-schools-opens-February-10-2025.aspx#:~:text=The%20MoE%20urges%20parents%20to,for%20arranging%20textbooks%20and%20transportation)). Emirati students are only permitted to attend schools offering specific approved curricula and cannot enroll in schools rated 'Weak' by the Dubai regulator ([citizens.me](https://citizens.me/ar/policies/school/#:~:text=,the%20Dubai%20Schools%20Inspection%20Bureau)). There is no mechanism of ranked school choices and no single algorithm assigning students in Dubai ([www.thenationalnews.com](https://www.thenationalnews.com/uae/education/2023/07/07/enrol-child-school-dubai-abu-dhabi/#:~:text=The%20earlier%20you%20apply%20the,school%20that%20matches%20their%20criteria)). Families arriving mid-year or late in the admissions cycle must contact schools individually to find open seats ([www.thenationalnews.com](https://www.thenationalnews.com/uae/education/2023/07/07/enrol-child-school-dubai-abu-dhabi/#:~:text=The%20earlier%20you%20apply%20the,school%20that%20matches%20their%20criteria)). Therefore, Dubai does not operate a Coordinated Choice and Assignment System (CCAS) for primary education.

In Dubai, secondary school admissions are not managed through any citywide Coordinated Choice and Assignment System (CCAS). Instead, the process is largely decentralized. The vast majority of students (over 90%) attend private secondary schools ([en.wikipedia.org](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Education_in_Dubai#:~:text=education%20sector,schools%20offering%2017%20different%20curricula)), and each private school conducts its own admissions, typically requiring parents to select a school and apply directly ([www.dubai.ae](https://www.dubai.ae/education#:~:text=To%20enroll%20a%20student%20in,placement%20tests%20for%20the%20child)). These schools may set their own admission criteria (such as placement tests or sibling preferences), and many popular schools maintain waiting lists when full ([www.thenationalnews.com](https://www.thenationalnews.com/uae/education/2023/12/28/waitlists-at-some-dubai-private-schools-before-january-term/#:~:text=Some%20Dubai%20private%20schools%20have,several%20reporting%20they%20are%20full)). Public secondary schools (serving mainly UAE citizens) have a centrally administered enrollment process via the federal Emirates Schools Establishment (ESE) ([www.dubai.ae](https://www.dubai.ae/education#:~:text=Public%20schools%20and%20kindergartens%20are,Visit)) ([www.dubai.ae](https://www.dubai.ae/education#:~:text=managed%20by%20the%20Emirates%20Schools,of%20rejection%20of%20the%20application)). However, this system does not involve students ranking multiple school preferences or a centralized matching algorithm - placements are based on eligibility (e.g., citizenship and available seats) rather than a citywide allocation mechanism. As a result, Dubai’s secondary education admissions are classified as Uncoordinated, with no single-offer algorithm governing school assignments.

Dubai’s tertiary admissions are centrally managed for Emirati students through the National Admissions and Placement Office (NAPO) under the UAE Ministry of Education ([ae.ok.com](https://ae.ok.com/content/en/blog/admissions-and-registration-office-in-the-uae-361480909481971712/#:~:text=Image%20The%20NAPO%20UAE%20platform,and%20children%20of%20Emirati%20nationals)). Applicants submit a unified application to multiple public universities (such as UAE University, Zayed University, and Higher Colleges of Technology) instead of applying to each separately ([www.thenationalnews.com](https://www.thenationalnews.com/uae/education/uae-students-given-deadline-for-higher-education-application-amendments-1.102962#:~:text=The%20National%20Admissions%20and%20Placement,off%20date)). Historically, students had to take the Emirates Standardized Test (EmSAT) in core subjects and meet GPA requirements for their desired programmes ([ae.ok.com](https://ae.ok.com/content/en/blog/admissions-and-registration-office-in-the-uae-361480909481971712/#:~:text=To%20register%20on%20NAPO%20UAE,Exam%20in%20the%20following%20subjects)). Following the cancellation of EmSAT in 2024, admissions now focus on secondary school grades, giving extra weight to high scores in subjects relevant to the student’s chosen field of study ([www.khaleejtimes.com](https://www.khaleejtimes.com/uae/education/uae-clarifies-new-student-admission-policy-as-emsat-is-cancelled#:~:text=To%20streamline%20university%20admissions%2C%20specific,strengths%20in%20their%20chosen%20field)). A recent overhaul of the system (NAPO 2.0) has removed strict limits on choices – students can apply to an unlimited number of institutions and programs, with applications and admissions processed on a rolling basis throughout the year ([thelawreporters.com](https://thelawreporters.com/uae-grants-universities-greater-autonomy-in-setting-admission-criteria-and-evaluation#:~:text=The%20revamped%20NAPO%202,explore%20multiple%20opportunities%20with%20ease)). Notably, NAPO’s centralized process ensures each applicant receives only one offer, and authorities assist any student who does not initially gain admission so that “no students are left behind” ([www.khaleejtimes.com](https://www.khaleejtimes.com/uae/education/uae-new-system-provides-easier-access-to-higher-education-says-minister#:~:text=%E2%80%9CWe%20don%27t%20want%20any%20students,with%20matching%20programmes%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20added)). (Private universities in Dubai are not part of NAPO and continue to conduct independent admissions, with expatriate students applying directly to those institutions ([ae.ok.com](https://ae.ok.com/content/en/blog/admissions-and-registration-office-in-the-uae-361480909481971712/#:~:text=The%20Admission%20and%20Registration%20Department,each%20institution%E2%80%99s%20individual%20admission%20criteria)).)

Sharjah does not operate a centralized school choice lottery or matching system for primary education. Admissions to public primary schools are managed by the Ministry of Education through a registration portal, which allocates students to schools based on residence area and seat availability rather than parental preference rankings ([www.moe.gov.ae](https://www.moe.gov.ae/En/MediaCenter/News/Pages/Registration-for-the-2025-2026-academic-year-in-public-schools-opens-February-10-2025.aspx#:~:text=The%20MoE%20urges%20parents%20to,for%20arranging%20textbooks%20and%20transportation)). Private primary schools in Sharjah conduct their own admissions independently (often on a first-come, first-served basis) without any city-wide coordination ([sharjahpublicschool.com](https://sharjahpublicschool.com/admission/#:~:text=Seats%20are%20available%20on%20a,served%20basis)). There is no evidence of a Coordinated Choice and Assignment System in Sharjah’s primary education; families typically enroll children in their local government school or apply directly to individual schools, and no unified algorithm or multi-school preference process is used.

Sharjah does not use a centralized school choice algorithm for secondary school placements ([www.thenationalnews.com](https://www.thenationalnews.com/uae/education/2023/07/07/enrol-child-school-dubai-abu-dhabi/#:~:text=Parents%20will%20need%20to%20speak,school%20that%20matches%20their%20criteria)). Admissions for public and private secondary schools are handled separately by each school or the respective authority. Public (government) schools generally enroll students based on local catchment areas (managed by the Ministry of Education/Emirates Schools Establishment), rather than through a citywide school choice system ([www.arada.com](https://www.arada.com/en/how-to-choose-a-school-in-sharjah/#:~:text=When%20it%20comes%20to%20primary,many%20students%20and%20teachers%20are)). Private schools in Sharjah manage admissions independently, often granting seats on a first-come, first-served basis and giving priority to siblings of current students ([www.scribd.com](https://www.scribd.com/document/815010672/Circular-for-Admission#:~:text=we%20wish%20to%20give%20the,collected%20from%20the%20School%20Office)). Families must apply to each desired school individually, as there is no unified application to rank multiple school preferences ([www.thenationalnews.com](https://www.thenationalnews.com/uae/education/2023/07/07/enrol-child-school-dubai-abu-dhabi/#:~:text=Parents%20will%20need%20to%20speak,school%20that%20matches%20their%20criteria)). No coordinated choice and assignment system has been implemented in Sharjah’s secondary education, and no major reforms in this regard have been reported.

Sharjah does not have a city-wide coordinated tertiary admission system. Each university (e.g. University of Sharjah, American University of Sharjah) runs its own admissions. The UAE Ministry of Education’s National Admissions and Placement Office (NAPO) provides a central admissions portal for Emirati students and children of Emirati mothers ([spaa.ae](https://spaa.ae/blog/news-2/sharjah-performing-arts-academy-joins-national-unified-registration-system-2225#:~:text=The%20National%20Admissions%20and%20Placement,academic%20criteria%20of%20each%20institution)). Through NAPO, students can apply to multiple universities in one process (over 30 participating institutions across the UAE) ([spaa.ae](https://spaa.ae/blog/news-2/sharjah-performing-arts-academy-joins-national-unified-registration-system-2225#:~:text=the%20specific%20academic%20criteria%20of,each%20institution)). Applicants submit a preference list (previously up to 5 choices, expanded to unlimited in 2024) ([ae.ok.com](https://ae.ok.com/content/en/blog/admissions-and-registration-office-in-the-uae-361480909481971712/#:~:text=match%20at%20L74%20,student%E2%80%99s%20academic%20track%20or%20curriculum)) ([thelawreporters.com](https://thelawreporters.com/uae-grants-universities-greater-autonomy-in-setting-admission-criteria-and-evaluation#:~:text=eligibility%20for%20specific%20majors)). NAPO is limited to nationals; non-Emirati applicants must apply directly to institutions ([ae.ok.com](https://ae.ok.com/content/en/blog/admissions-and-registration-office-in-the-uae-361480909481971712/#:~:text=The%20Admission%20and%20Registration%20Department,each%20institution%E2%80%99s%20individual%20admission%20criteria)). Admission decisions under NAPO are mainly based on academic performance (high school grades and standardized tests like EmSAT) ([spaa.ae](https://spaa.ae/blog/news-2/sharjah-performing-arts-academy-joins-national-unified-registration-system-2225#:~:text=centralised%20admissions%20system%20for%20UAE,academic%20criteria%20of%20each%20institution)), and each institution makes the final offer decision, with students confirming one offer to finalize enrollment ([ae.ok.com](https://ae.ok.com/content/en/blog/admissions-and-registration-office-in-the-uae-361480909481971712/#:~:text=1,and%20communicate%20with%20the%20institution)). In late 2024, the NAPO system was overhauled (NAPO 2.0) to increase flexibility and access ([thelawreporters.com](https://thelawreporters.com/uae-grants-universities-greater-autonomy-in-setting-admission-criteria-and-evaluation#:~:text=After%20the%20UAE%20canceled%20the,objectives%20to%20maintain%20quality%20outcomes)). Overall, tertiary admissions in Sharjah remain largely uncoordinated with no single city-run assignment algorithm.

Buenos Aires operates a centralized school choice system for public primary schools. Families must pre-register online and submit a ranked list of preferred public schools (up to eight choices) ([buenosaires.gob.ar](https://buenosaires.gob.ar/educacion/preguntas-frecuentes#:~:text=%C2%BFPuedo%20agregar%20opciones%20alternativas%20a,que%20me%20da%20el%20sistema)). A city-wide algorithm then assigns each student a single school seat based on the family’s preference order and the schools’ admission priorities ([buenosaires.gob.ar](https://buenosaires.gob.ar/noticias/publicacion-de-listados-de-asignacion-de-vacantes-de-la-primera-etapa#:~:text=Cabe%20recordar%20que%20la%20asignaci%C3%B3n,condiciones%20de%20ingreso%20entre%20aspirantes)). Priority is given to applicants with siblings already in the school, those coming from the school’s own kindergarten, children of school staff or single working parents (family-related criteria), and those living near the school or in vulnerable socio-economic situations (e.g. residing in family shelters) ([boletinoficial.buenosaires.gob.ar](https://boletinoficial.buenosaires.gob.ar/normativaba/norma/31301#:~:text=Hermanos%20de%20alumnos%20del%20establecimiento)) ([boletinoficial.buenosaires.gob.ar](https://boletinoficial.buenosaires.gob.ar/normativaba/norma/31301#:~:text=Menor%20distancia%20del%20domicilio%20con,a%20menor%20distancia%20del%20domicilio)). When demand exceeds capacity within a priority group, a random lottery number (Sorteo Público Anual) is used to break ties fairly ([buenosaires.gob.ar](https://buenosaires.gob.ar/asignacion-de-vacantes#:~:text=Record%C3%A1%20que%20en%20caso%20de,de%20la%20asignaci%C3%B3n%20de%20vacantes)). This coordinated system, first established by a 2013 resolution ([boletinoficial.buenosaires.gob.ar](https://boletinoficial.buenosaires.gob.ar/normativaba/norma/815270#:~:text=Que%20mediante%20la%20Resoluci%C3%B3n%203337,Sistema%20de%20Inscripciones%20en)), replaced the prior decentralized enrollment process. It has since been updated (most recently reformed in 2025) to refine its rules and ensure a transparent, equitable assignment of primary school places across the city ([boletinoficial.buenosaires.gob.ar](https://boletinoficial.buenosaires.gob.ar/normativaba/norma/815270#:~:text=S%C3%ADntesis%3A)).

Buenos Aires City (CABA) operates a centralized online admission system for all public (state-run) secondary schools. Families submit an online application with a ranked list of up to 8 school choices ([buenosaires.gob.ar](https://buenosaires.gob.ar/educacion/preguntas-frecuentes#:~:text=S%C3%AD%2C%20en%20funci%C3%B3n%20de%20los,acuerdo%20al%20nivel%20educativo%20seleccionado)). After the application period, a single assignment is generated for each student based on stated preferences and priority criteria, using a centralized algorithm ([buenosaires.gob.ar](https://buenosaires.gob.ar/asignacion-de-vacantes#:~:text=La%20asignaci%C3%B3n%20de%20vacantes%20se,distintos%20niveles%20educativos%20y%20modalidades)). The algorithm follows an *Immediate Acceptance (Boston)* mechanism, meaning schools fill seats in rounds by applicants’ preference rank; therefore, listing a school at a lower rank can reduce an applicant’s chance even if they have priority there ([buenosaires.gob.ar](https://buenosaires.gob.ar/educacion/preguntas-frecuentes#:~:text=%C2%BFC%C3%B3mo%20incide%20el%20orden%20en,en%20la%20asignaci%C3%B3n%20de%20vacantes)). The assignment prioritizes students with siblings already enrolled at the school, those living near the school or with a parent working nearby (proximity), children of school staff or participants in certain programs, and applicants facing socio-economic disadvantages (e.g., unsatisfied basic needs) ([aldiaargentina.microjuris.com](https://aldiaargentina.microjuris.com/2021/03/03/fallos-caba-el-otorgamiento-de-vacantes-a-la-educacion-inicial-no-obligatoria-debe-efectuarse-de-acuerdo-a-los-grupos-prioritarios-y-quien-no-la-obtiene-no-tiene-derecho-a-obtener-un-subsidio-para/#:~:text=1,en%20una%20instituci%C3%B3n%20bajo%20convenio)) ([aldiaargentina.microjuris.com](https://aldiaargentina.microjuris.com/2021/03/03/fallos-caba-el-otorgamiento-de-vacantes-a-la-educacion-inicial-no-obligatoria-debe-efectuarse-de-acuerdo-a-los-grupos-prioritarios-y-quien-no-la-obtiene-no-tiene-derecho-a-obtener-un-subsidio-para/#:~:text=6,en%20hoteles%20familiares%20o%20pensiones)). Any ties are broken by an annual lottery ([buenosaires.gob.ar](https://buenosaires.gob.ar/asignacion-de-vacantes#:~:text=Record%C3%A1%20que%20en%20caso%20de,de%20la%20asignaci%C3%B3n%20de%20vacantes)). The first city-wide coordinated system was implemented in 2013 ([buenosaires.gob.ar](https://buenosaires.gob.ar/noticias/nuevo-sistema-de-inscripcion-la-escuela-publica#:~:text=El%20n%C3%BAmero%20es%20el%20resultado,Se%C3%B1al%20de%20confianza)), and the policy framework was updated with a new enrollment regulation in 2024–2025 ([boletinoficial.buenosaires.gob.ar](https://boletinoficial.buenosaires.gob.ar/normativaba/norma/815270#:~:text=S%C3%ADntesis%3A)). Private schools in Buenos Aires manage admissions independently, outside of this centralized system.

Buenos Aires does not have a coordinated central assignment system for tertiary education. Instead, students apply directly to individual universities or tertiary institutes, and each institution sets its own admission requirements and selection process ([www.edarabia.com](https://www.edarabia.com/how-apply-university-argentina/#:~:text=5,evaluation%20criteria%20for%20international%20admissions)). Public universities (such as the University of Buenos Aires) generally have open or unrestricted admissions (often with leveling courses or introductory cycles) or their own entrance exams, and private universities conduct their own exams or evaluations ([www.timeshighereducation.com](https://www.timeshighereducation.com/counsellor/admissions-processes-and-funding/applying-university-argentina-essential-guide#:~:text=Most%20Argentinian%20universities%20accept%20online,school%20average%20above%208%2F10%20points)). The Buenos Aires city government provides an online portal for its public tertiary institutes (e.g. technical training colleges and teacher training institutes) to manage applications, but placement is handled on a per-institution basis. Oversubscribed city-run programs use either entrance examinations (with admission based on exam score ranking) or random lotteries to allocate available seats ([buenosaires.gob.ar](https://buenosaires.gob.ar/salud/docencia-investigacion-y-desarrollo-profesional/sistema-de-ingreso/ingreso-2022#:~:text=Este%20examen%20definir%C3%A1%20tu%20ingreso,examen%20ser%C3%A1%20de%2060%20minutos)) ([ens6-caba.infd.edu.ar](https://ens6-caba.infd.edu.ar/sitio/inscripciones-2/#:~:text=,ar)). Consequently, there is no single centralized algorithm that produces one offer per applicant across all tertiary institutions in the city.

Córdoba’s primary school admissions are managed through a centralized online system introduced in 2020, covering all public (state-run) schools ([www.cba.gov.ar](https://www.cba.gov.ar/escuelas-la-preinscripcion-para-ingresantes-se-hara-a-traves-de-cidi/#:~:text=El%20gobierno%20provincial%2C%20a%20trav%C3%A9s,en%20escuelas%20del%20sector%20estatal)) ([hoydia.com.ar](https://hoydia.com.ar/informacion-general/abren-las-preinscripciones-escolares-para-ingresantes-todo-lo-que-hay-que-saber/#:~:text=El%20Ministerio%20de%20Educaci%C3%B3n%20de,para%20el%20ciclo%20lectivo%202025)). Parents register on the provincial digital platform (CiDi) and submit a ranked preference list of 2–4 schools for their child ([www.cba.gov.ar](https://www.cba.gov.ar/escuelas-la-preinscripcion-para-ingresantes-se-hara-a-traves-de-cidi/#:~:text=portal%20de%20Ciudadano%20Digital%20,o%20si%20le%20es%20indistinto)). After the application window closes, a single school is assigned to each student according to available seats and set priority criteria ([www.cba.gov.ar](https://www.cba.gov.ar/finalizo-el-proceso-de-preinscripciones-escolares-2025-en-cordoba/#:~:text=,recibir%20los%20resultados%20de%20asignaci%C3%B3n)) ([www.cba.gov.ar](https://www.cba.gov.ar/comienzan-las-preinscripciones-escolares-para-ingresantes-2025/#:~:text=Culminado%20el%20plazo%20para%20la,y%20seg%C3%BAn%20los%20siguientes%20criterios)). Top priority is given to students continuing in the same academic unit (e.g., from an affiliated preschool), followed by those with siblings already at the school, and then those living in the same neighborhood ([www.cba.gov.ar](https://www.cba.gov.ar/comienzan-las-preinscripciones-escolares-para-ingresantes-2025/#:~:text=,las%20vacantes%20disponibles%20se%20sortear%C3%A1n)). Any remaining seats are allocated by random lottery among the other applicants ([www.cba.gov.ar](https://www.cba.gov.ar/comienzan-las-preinscripciones-escolares-para-ingresantes-2025/#:~:text=validada%20por%20el%20establecimiento%20educativo,aspirantes%20mediante%20un%20proceso%20aleatorio)). The centralized assignment results are published to families via their CiDi accounts ([www.cba.gov.ar](https://www.cba.gov.ar/finalizo-el-proceso-de-preinscripciones-escolares-2025-en-cordoba/#:~:text=,recibir%20los%20resultados%20de%20asignaci%C3%B3n)). Private schools in Córdoba are not part of this coordinated system and handle admissions independently ([www.cba.gov.ar](https://www.cba.gov.ar/escuelas-la-preinscripcion-para-ingresantes-se-hara-a-traves-de-cidi/#:~:text=En%20las%20escuelas%20de%20gesti%C3%B3n,ser%C3%A1%20estipulado%20por%20cada%20instituci%C3%B3n)). In 2025, the pre-registration timeline was moved up to late August – mid September (for the 2026 school year) to streamline planning ([crecerhoy.com](https://crecerhoy.com/padres/preinscripciones-escolares-en-cordoba-las-fechas-clave-para-el-ciclo-lectivo-2026/#:~:text=Desde%20el%2025%20de%20agosto,niveles%20inicial%2C%20primario%20y%20secundario)). The core matching algorithm is not publicly specified, but it is centrally run with lottery tie-breakers to ensure fairness ([www.cba.gov.ar](https://www.cba.gov.ar/escuelas-la-preinscripcion-para-ingresantes-se-hara-a-traves-de-cidi/#:~:text=,por%20un%20organismo%20externo%20especializado)).

Córdoba (Argentina) operates a centralized admissions system for public secondary schools. Families apply online through the provincial Ciudadano Digital (CiDi) platform using a single Formulario Único de Postulantes, listing up to four preferred schools in order of choice ([www.cba.gov.ar](https://www.cba.gov.ar/comienzan-las-preinscripciones-escolares-para-ingresantes-2025/#:~:text=La%20persona%20responsable%20del%20estudiante,y%20tambi%C3%A9n%20seleccionar%20el%20turno)). After the application window, the provincial Ministry of Education assigns each student to one school based on available seats and set priorities ([www.cba.gov.ar](https://www.cba.gov.ar/abrio-la-preinscripcion-a-niveles-inicial-primario-y-medio/#:~:text=Culminado%20el%20plazo%20para%20la,y%20seg%C3%BAn%20los%20siguientes%20criterios)) ([www.cba.gov.ar](https://www.cba.gov.ar/abrio-la-preinscripcion-a-niveles-inicial-primario-y-medio/#:~:text=Finalmente%2C%C2%A0el%20lunes%2030%20de%20noviembre,de%20Gesti%C3%B3n%20de%20Estudiantes%2C%20quienes)). Priority is given to students continuing from an affiliated primary (same unidad académica), those with siblings already attending, and those residing in the school's neighborhood ([www.cba.gov.ar](https://www.cba.gov.ar/comienzan-las-preinscripciones-escolares-para-ingresantes-2025/#:~:text=,aspirantes%20mediante%20un%20proceso%20aleatorio)). If applicants still outnumber seats after these criteria, remaining places are allocated by random lottery ([www.cba.gov.ar](https://www.cba.gov.ar/comienzan-las-preinscripciones-escolares-para-ingresantes-2025/#:~:text=,aspirantes%20mediante%20un%20proceso%20aleatorio)). Only a single offer is issued per student, and results are communicated via the CiDi portal ([www.cba.gov.ar](https://www.cba.gov.ar/abrio-la-preinscripcion-a-niveles-inicial-primario-y-medio/#:~:text=Finalmente%2C%C2%A0el%20lunes%2030%20de%20noviembre,de%20Gesti%C3%B3n%20de%20Estudiantes%2C%20quienes)). This coordinated system was first implemented in 2020 for the 2021 school year ([www.cba.gov.ar](https://www.cba.gov.ar/abrio-la-preinscripcion-a-niveles-inicial-primario-y-medio/#:~:text=)). It covers all state-run (public) secondary institutions in Córdoba, while private schools continue to manage admissions independently ([www.cba.gov.ar](https://www.cba.gov.ar/abrio-la-preinscripcion-a-niveles-inicial-primario-y-medio/#:~:text=En%20las%20escuelas%20de%20gesti%C3%B3n,ser%C3%A1%20estipulado%20por%20cada%20instituci%C3%B3n)). No major reforms to the assignment mechanism have been reported since its introduction.

Córdoba, Argentina does not utilize any centralized tertiary admission system. Each university or higher education institution conducts its own admissions independently, without a unified application or matching algorithm ([www.scielo.org.mx](https://www.scielo.org.mx/scielo.php?lng=es&nrm=iso&pid=S0185-27602023000300104&script=sci_arttext#:~:text=La%20LES%20habilit%C3%B3%20sistemas%20de,En)). Applicants do not submit ranked preferences across multiple institutions; they apply directly to individual universities or programs. By national law, all secondary school graduates have the right to free and unrestricted access to undergraduate education ([larepublica.pe](https://larepublica.pe/mundo/2022/03/20/universidades-con-ingreso-libre-en-argentina-como-funciona-el-modelo-a-diferencia-de-otros-paises-del-mundo-ley-de-educacion-superior#:~:text=%C2%BFExiste%20alguna%20limitaci%C3%B3n%20para%20ingresar,a%20la%20educaci%C3%B3n%20superior)). Some institutions may require leveling courses or entrance exams for certain programs, but these processes are implemented at the institution or faculty level and not by an external centralized authority ([www.scielo.org.mx](https://www.scielo.org.mx/scielo.php?lng=es&nrm=iso&pid=S0185-27602023000300104&script=sci_arttext#:~:text=La%20LES%20habilit%C3%B3%20sistemas%20de,En)) ([larepublica.pe](https://larepublica.pe/mundo/2022/03/20/universidades-con-ingreso-libre-en-argentina-como-funciona-el-modelo-a-diferencia-de-otros-paises-del-mundo-ley-de-educacion-superior#:~:text=%C2%BFExiste%20alguna%20limitaci%C3%B3n%20para%20ingresar,a%20la%20educaci%C3%B3n%20superior)). In 2015, Argentina’s Higher Education Law was reformed to reinforce the principle of open admission and limit selective entry practices ([www.scielo.org.mx](https://www.scielo.org.mx/scielo.php?lng=es&nrm=iso&pid=S0185-27602023000300104&script=sci_arttext#:~:text=La%20pol%C3%ADtica%20nacional%20de%20acceso,el%20acceso%20a%20la%20Universidad)) ([www.scielo.org.mx](https://www.scielo.org.mx/scielo.php?lng=es&nrm=iso&pid=S0185-27602023000300104&script=sci_arttext#:~:text=Con%20relaci%C3%B3n%20al%20acceso%20a,el%20art%C3%ADculo%207%C2%B0%20indic%C3%B3%20que)). As a result, tertiary admissions in Córdoba remain uncoordinated, with no single assignment mechanism or common priority criteria used citywide.

Corrientes province’s primary school admissions use a centralized online system for public schools, where families submit a ranked list of preferred schools (up to 10 choices as of 2025) ([www.corrientespositiva.com.ar](https://www.corrientespositiva.com.ar/notix/noticia/66298/preinscripcin-online-permitir-seleccionar-hasta-diez-escuelas.htm#:~:text=Para%20el%20ciclo%20lectivo%202026%2C,ar)). The Ministry of Education assigns each student a single seat via a lottery-based algorithm, incorporating priority criteria ([www.mec.gob.ar](https://www.mec.gob.ar/inscripcion-aspirantes/#:~:text=1,De%20lo%20contrario)). Priority is given to top academic performers (flag-bearing students), siblings of current students, children of school staff, and pupils from directly affiliated preschools ([www.mec.gob.ar](https://www.mec.gob.ar/inscripcion-aspirantes/#:~:text=1,la%20pregunta%3A%20si%20el%20aspirante)). This coordinated system has been in place for several years, replacing the old practice of overnight lines at school gates ([corrientesenelaire.com.ar](https://corrientesenelaire.com.ar/noticia/23387_inscripciones-online-se-podr-elegir-hasta-diez-establecimientos.htm#:~:text=La%20provincia%20dej%C3%B3%20de%20lado,al%20menos%20para%20conseguir%20vacantes)). A reform in 2025 doubled the number of allowable school choices from five to ten to improve the chances of securing a spot in the first round ([www.corrientespositiva.com.ar](https://www.corrientespositiva.com.ar/notix/noticia/66298/preinscripcin-online-permitir-seleccionar-hasta-diez-escuelas.htm#:~:text=Seg%C3%BAn%20periodos%20anteriores%2C%20las%20familias,podr%C3%A1n%20elegir%20la%20cantidad%20existente)). Only state-run (public) schools participate in this centralized admission; private schools in Corrientes handle their admissions separately ([corrientesenlinea.com](https://corrientesenlinea.com/sociedad/corrientes-confirmaron-las-fechas-de-inscripcion-online-para-el-ciclo-lectivo-2026/#:~:text=El%20sistema%20estar%C3%A1%20habilitado%20para,hijos%20en%20instituciones%20educativas%20p%C3%BAblicas)).

Corrientes (Argentina) uses a centralized online admission system for public secondary schools ([www.ellitoral.com.ar](https://www.ellitoral.com.ar/sociedad/2025-10-17-19-14-0-corrientes-abre-las-inscripciones-online-para-el-ciclo-lectivo-2026-cuando-y-como-anotarse#:~:text=El%20sistema%20permitir%C3%A1%20elegir%20hasta,para%20ingresar%20a%20instituciones%20estatales)). Families register via the provincial portal and rank up to eight preferred schools ([www.corrientesteinforma.com.ar](https://www.corrientesteinforma.com.ar/mobile/inicio/noticia/49223/Corrientes-habilita-la-inscripcin-escolar-2026-gua-paso-a-paso-para-elegir.html#:~:text=El%20tr%C3%A1mite%20se%20realizar%C3%A1%20solo,Por%20PGDJ)). After the application window, a single assignment is made through an electronic lottery that accounts for preferences and priority criteria ([www.ellitoral.com.ar](https://www.ellitoral.com.ar/sociedad/2025-10-17-19-14-0-corrientes-abre-las-inscripciones-online-para-el-ciclo-lectivo-2026-cuando-y-como-anotarse#:~:text=Carlos%20Encinas%2C%20director%20de%20Sistemas,alguna%20de%20las%20escuelas%20seleccionadas)) ([www.mec.gob.ar](https://www.mec.gob.ar/inscripcion-aspirantes/#:~:text=1,otro%20aspirante%20sin%20prioridad%20registrada)). Priority is given to applicants with siblings already attending the school, children of school staff, top academic performers (flag bearers), and students from feeder ("associated") schools ([corrientesaldia.info](https://corrientesaldia.info/2025/10/27/comienza-la-inscripcion-para-el-ciclo-lectivo-2026-en-las-escuelas-publicas-de-corrientes/#:~:text=El%20funcionario%20detall%C3%B3%20que%20existen,Tendr%C3%A1n%20preferencia)). This system, managed by the Corrientes Ministry of Education, ensures each student receives one offer and replaces the old first-come first-served approach, improving transparency and fairness ([www.corrientespositiva.com.ar](https://www.corrientespositiva.com.ar/notix/noticia/66298/preinscripcin-online-permitir-seleccionar-hasta-diez-escuelas.htm#:~:text=Con%20este%20procedimiento%20que%20se,las%20puertas%20de%20los%20establecimientos)). The coordinated enrollment process has been in place since late 2020 (for the 2021 school year) ([www.mec.gob.ar](https://www.mec.gob.ar/ciclo-lectivo-2021-las-inscripciones-seran-solo-online-desde-el-9-y-el-23-de-diciembre/#:~:text=Se%20trata%20del%20espacio%20inscripciones,o%20primer%20a%C3%B1o%20de%20secundaria)). A recent reform in 2025 expanded the maximum number of school choices from five to eight to increase the chances of securing a spot ([www.mec.gob.ar](https://www.mec.gob.ar/ciclo-lectivo-2021-las-inscripciones-seran-solo-online-desde-el-9-y-el-23-de-diciembre/#:~:text=Seg%C3%BAn%20adelantaron%2C%20se%20podr%C3%A1%20optar,finalice%20el%20per%C3%ADodo%20de%20inscripci%C3%B3n)) ([www.ellitoral.com.ar](https://www.ellitoral.com.ar/sociedad/2025-10-17-19-14-0-corrientes-abre-las-inscripciones-online-para-el-ciclo-lectivo-2026-cuando-y-como-anotarse#:~:text=Una%20de%20las%20principales%20novedades,facilitar%20la%20asignaci%C3%B3n%20de%20vacantes)). Note that the coordinated system covers state-run schools only; private schools in Corrientes handle admissions independently.

Corrientes Province operates a centralized assignment system for tertiary non-university institutions (teacher training colleges and technical institutes). Applicants submit applications via the SIMA portal and can list up to two preferred programs ([www.mec.gob.ar](https://www.mec.gob.ar/pre-inscripcion-a-carreras-del-nivel-superior/#:~:text=Los%20interesados%20deber%C3%A1n%20ingresar%20a,profesorados%20o%20tecnicaturas)). A central algorithm allocates seats through a random lottery, so no first-come advantage or academic selection is used ([www.mec.gob.ar](https://www.mec.gob.ar/pre-inscripcion-a-carreras-del-nivel-superior/#:~:text=La%20asignaci%C3%B3n%20de%20cupos%20se,disponibles%20en%20la%20Plataforma%20Sima)). Each candidate receives at most one offer, notified by email and on the SIMA platform ([www.mec.gob.ar](https://www.mec.gob.ar/pre-inscripcion-a-carreras-del-nivel-superior/#:~:text=La%20asignaci%C3%B3n%20de%20cupos%20se,disponibles%20en%20la%20Plataforma%20Sima)). The CCAS encompasses public provincial institutes and also includes private institutes under provincial oversight ([sima.mec.gob.ar](https://sima.mec.gob.ar/#:~:text=Institutos%20Gesti%C3%B3n%20Estatal)). No specific priority criteria (such as exam scores or proximity) are applied beyond the equal-chance lottery ([www.mec.gob.ar](https://www.mec.gob.ar/pre-inscripcion-a-carreras-del-nivel-superior/#:~:text=La%20asignaci%C3%B3n%20de%20cupos%20se,disponibles%20en%20la%20Plataforma%20Sima)). This system has been in place in recent years, though the exact implementation year and any major reforms are not publicly documented. (Admissions to national universities in Corrientes continue to be managed separately by each institution outside of this system.)

Primary school admissions in Mendoza are managed through a stepwise procedure rather than a centralized choice system. Families do not submit ranked school preferences; instead, registration occurs at individual schools in sequential instances defined by the provincial education authority (DGE) ([www.mendoza.gov.ar](https://www.mendoza.gov.ar/prensa/inscripcion-para-el-ingreso-a-primer-grado-ciclo-lectivo-2022/#:~:text=Tercera%20instancia%3A%2010%20de%20setiembre)). Priority is given to specific groups in order: children with disabilities (preferably at the nearest school) ([www.mendoza.gov.ar](https://www.mendoza.gov.ar/prensa/inscripcion-para-el-ingreso-a-primer-grado-ciclo-lectivo-2022/#:~:text=Primera%20instancia%3A%207%20de%20setiembre)), siblings of current students and children of school staff ([www.mendoza.gov.ar](https://www.mendoza.gov.ar/prensa/inscripcion-para-el-ingreso-a-primer-grado-ciclo-lectivo-2022/#:~:text=Inscripci%C3%B3n%20directa%20para%20hermanos%20y,Primario%20con%20la%20que%20articula)), and children attending feeder kindergartens ([www.mendoza.gov.ar](https://www.mendoza.gov.ar/prensa/inscripcion-para-el-ingreso-a-primer-grado-ciclo-lectivo-2022/#:~:text=Segunda%20instancia%3A%209%20de%20setiembre)). Subsequently, new applicants may apply to schools, with priority for those who live or work nearby ([www.mendoza.edu.ar](https://www.mendoza.edu.ar/comienzan-las-inscripciones-para-el-ingreso-a-primer-grado-2026/#:~:text=,educativas%20publicar%C3%A1n%20las%20vacantes%20otorgadas)). Any child still without a seat after these rounds is assigned to a school with available space by the education authorities ([www.mendoza.edu.ar](https://www.mendoza.edu.ar/comienzan-las-inscripciones-para-el-ingreso-a-primer-grado-2026/#:~:text=Cuarta%20instancia)). This process covers public schools (escuelas de gestión estatal) ([www.mendoza.gov.ar](https://www.mendoza.gov.ar/prensa/ciclo-lectivo-2025-comienzan-las-instancias-de-la-inscripcion-para-primer-grado/#:~:text=La%20Direcci%C3%B3n%20General%20de%20Escuelas%2C,las%20escuelas%20de%20gesti%C3%B3n%20estatal)); private schools conduct their admissions independently. Because there is no centralized algorithm generating a single offer per student, Mendoza's primary education admissions system is classified as uncoordinated.

Mendoza (Argentina) uses a coordinated centralized assignment system for public secondary school admissions ([www.mdzol.com](https://www.mdzol.com/sociedad/2024/10/18/nuevo-sistema-de-inscripcion-para-secundaria-en-mendoza-que-cambia-en-2025-1160292.html#:~:text=Mendoza%29.%20,y%20la%20disponibilidad%20de%20vacantes)) ([www.mdzol.com](https://www.mdzol.com/sociedad/2023/11/1/confirmaron-las-fechas-de-inscripciones-al-nivel-secundario-380740.html#:~:text=Aspirantes%20para%20realizar%20el%20nivel,sobre%20el%20proceso%20de%20inscripci%C3%B3n)). The process is managed by the provincial education authority (DGE) and consists of four stages. In Stage 1, students who meet certain criteria (e.g. siblings at the school, certified disabilities, top academic performers, local feeder school ties or proximity) pre-register in person at their preferred school ([www.mendoza.edu.ar](https://www.mendoza.edu.ar/ingreso-a-1-ano-de-secundaria-asi-sera-la-inscripcion-para-el-ciclo-lectivo-2021/#:~:text=,titulares%3A%20cuando%20los%20aspirantes%20superen)) ([www.mdzol.com](https://www.mdzol.com/sociedad/2024/10/18/nuevo-sistema-de-inscripcion-para-secundaria-en-mendoza-que-cambia-en-2025-1160292.html#:~:text=Uno%20de%20los%20puntos%20destacados,en%20la%20asignaci%C3%B3n%20de%20vacantes)). Next, in Stage 2, families list up to 5 preferred schools online via the GEM portal, and a centralized algorithm (run by DGE) assigns each student a single school seat based on their preferences and the schools' priority rules ([www.mendoza.edu.ar](https://www.mendoza.edu.ar/ingreso-a-secundaria-2025-ultimos-dias-para-la-segunda-instancia-de-inscripcion/#:~:text=,entre%20tres%20y%20cinco%20opciones)) ([www.mendoza.edu.ar](https://www.mendoza.edu.ar/comenzaron-las-inscripciones-para-primer-ano-de-secundaria-2017/#:~:text=24%20de%20octubre%3A%20procedimiento%20de,bancos%20por%20el%20sistema%20inform%C3%A1tico)). Unassigned students can then seek placement in Stage 3 at regional supervision offices and finally Stage 4 through the Secondary Education Directorate, which guarantees a slot for everyone remaining ([www.mendoza.gov.ar](https://www.mendoza.gov.ar/prensa/comienza-la-inscripcion-para-el-ingreso-a-secundaria/#:~:text=13%20al%2020%20de%20diciembre%3A,m%C3%A1s%20cercana%20a%20su%20domicilio)) ([www.mendoza.edu.ar](https://www.mendoza.edu.ar/ingreso-a-secundaria-2025-ultimos-dias-para-la-segunda-instancia-de-inscripcion/#:~:text=,asignados%20en%20las%20instancias%20anteriores)). Key priority criteria include sibling attendance, disability status, home–school distance (around 1 km radius), and academic merit (e.g., flag-bearing honor students) ([www.mdzol.com](https://www.mdzol.com/sociedad/2024/10/18/nuevo-sistema-de-inscripcion-para-secundaria-en-mendoza-que-cambia-en-2025-1160292.html#:~:text=Uno%20de%20los%20puntos%20destacados,en%20la%20asignaci%C3%B3n%20de%20vacantes)) ([www.mendoza.edu.ar](https://www.mendoza.edu.ar/ingreso-a-1-ano-de-secundaria-asi-sera-la-inscripcion-para-el-ciclo-lectivo-2021/#:~:text=,hasta%20cubrir%20el%20porcentaje%20referido)). Mendoza implemented this centralized admissions system around 2016 ([www.mendoza.edu.ar](https://www.mendoza.edu.ar/comenzaron-las-inscripciones-para-primer-ano-de-secundaria-2017/#:~:text=)) and introduced significant reforms by 2024 to improve fairness and efficiency ([www.mdzol.com](https://www.mdzol.com/sociedad/2024/10/18/nuevo-sistema-de-inscripcion-para-secundaria-en-mendoza-que-cambia-en-2025-1160292.html#:~:text=En%20medio%20de%20un%20panorama,y%20asegurar%20que%20el%20proceso)). Private secondary schools are not part of the CCAS and continue to administer their own admissions processes.

In Mendoza, there is no centralized choice and assignment system for tertiary education admissions. Each university or higher education institute conducts its own admission process, reflecting the autonomy granted by Argentine law ([www.redalyc.org](https://www.redalyc.org/journal/1531/153175977002/#:~:text=La%20diversidad%20de%20pol%C3%ADticas%20de,que%20no%20han%20desarrollado%20las)). Applicants do not submit ranked preferences to a central authority; instead, they apply directly to individual institutions. Admissions are generally open-access (ingreso irrestricto), requiring only a secondary school diploma, though some institutions use entrance exams or leveling courses to ensure basic competencies ([www.redalyc.org](https://www.redalyc.org/journal/1531/153175977002/#:~:text=para%20dictar%20sus%20propias%20normas,cumplimiento%20de%20diferentes%20instancias%20administrativas)) ([www.losandes.com.ar](https://www.losandes.com.ar/politica/la-dge-establecio-una-serie-cambios-el-ingreso-y-formacion-docente-cuales-son-n5959573#:~:text=El%20nuevo%20dispositivo%20no%20elimina,esenciales%20al%20iniciar%20sus%20carreras)). In 2025 the provincial education authority (DGE) introduced a unified entrance evaluation for teacher training and technical institutes (public and private) to standardize academic readiness ([www.mendoza.edu.ar](https://www.mendoza.edu.ar/resolucion-4708-dge-implementacion-dispositivo-de-ingreso-de-nivel-superior-institutos-de-formacion-docente-y-tecnica-2025/#:~:text=Determinar%20la%20implementaci%C3%B3n%20de%20un,2027%20en)) ([www.losandes.com.ar](https://www.losandes.com.ar/politica/la-dge-establecio-una-serie-cambios-el-ingreso-y-formacion-docente-cuales-son-n5959573#:~:text=%2A%20Segunda%20fase%20%282026,pedag%C3%B3gicos%20para%20garantizar%20la%20continuidad)). However, this is an academic requirement rather than a centralized matching algorithm, and it does not produce a single offer per applicant. As of the latest information, tertiary admissions in Mendoza remain uncoordinated in terms of a centralized algorithmic assignment.

([educacion.chaco.gob.ar](https://educacion.chaco.gob.ar/pre-inscripcion-2023/#:~:text=Es%20el%20sistema%20v%C3%ADa%20SIE,hasta%20dos%20escuelas%20de%20preferencia)) Resistencia (Chaco) operates a coordinated primary school admissions system via the SIE online platform, where families can list up to two preferred public schools.  ([chaco.gob.ar](https://chaco.gob.ar/noticia-comienza-la-preinscripcion-2026-para-los-niveles-inicial-y-primario-2025-10-30-08-06#:~:text=Las%20escuelas%20asignar%C3%A1n%20las%20vacantes,Estudiantes%20sin%20los%20criterios%20anteriores)) Student placement is governed by priority criteria – children of school staff, siblings of current students, those living within a 1 km radius of the school, and children of parents working in that radius – with a lottery tie-break for applicants sharing the same priority group.  ([chaco.gob.ar](https://chaco.gob.ar/noticia-comienza-la-preinscripcion-2026-para-los-niveles-inicial-y-primario-2025-10-30-08-06#:~:text=,Preferencia%202)) Seats are allocated in two rounds: first all first-choice applicants are placed (according to the priority order and tie-breaks), then remaining vacancies are offered to second-choice applicants. This procedure corresponds to the Immediate Acceptance (Boston) mechanism.  ([chaco.gob.ar](https://chaco.gob.ar/noticia-comienza-la-preinscripcion-2026-para-los-niveles-inicial-y-primario-2025-10-30-08-06#:~:text=La%20preinscripci%C3%B3n%20alcanza%20a%20escuelas,sistemas%20y%20plazos%20de%20inscripci%C3%B3n)) The centralized system covers state-run, social, and intercultural public schools; private primary schools in Resistencia are not included and continue to use their own admission processes.  ([www.chaco.gov.ar](https://www.chaco.gov.ar/noticia-ciclo-lectivo-2025-la-preinscripcion-en-nivel-secundario-sera-del-1-al-15-de-octubre-2024-09-29-19-00#:~:text=Por%20cuarto%20a%C3%B1o%20consecutivo%2C%20el,preinscriptos%20superen%20a%20las%20vacantes)) The CCAS was first implemented around 2021, and in 2024 a reform introduced entrance examinations for oversubscribed secondary schools (while primary school assignments remain based on the established priorities and lottery).

Resistencia (Chaco, Argentina) uses a centralized admission system for public secondary schools. Families submit up to two school preferences via an online platform (SIE) ([www.chaco.gov.ar](https://www.chaco.gov.ar/noticia-ciclo-lectivo-2025-la-preinscripcion-en-nivel-secundario-sera-del-1-al-15-de-octubre-2024-09-29-19-00#:~:text=REQUISITOS%20Los%20aspirantes%20a%20ingresar,En%20este%20sentido%2C%20tendr%C3%A1n)). Each student receives one assignment, determined by priorities and (if needed) an entrance exam ([www.chaco.gov.ar](https://www.chaco.gov.ar/noticia-ciclo-lectivo-2025-la-preinscripcion-en-nivel-secundario-sera-del-1-al-15-de-octubre-2024-09-29-19-00#:~:text=partir%20de%20este%20a%C3%B1o%20habr%C3%A1,hermanos%2Fas%20en%20el%20establecimiento%20escolar)). Children of the school’s staff and siblings of current students are given first priority ([www.chaco.gov.ar](https://www.chaco.gov.ar/noticia-ciclo-lectivo-2025-la-preinscripcion-en-nivel-secundario-sera-del-1-al-15-de-octubre-2024-09-29-19-00#:~:text=partir%20de%20este%20a%C3%B1o%20habr%C3%A1,hermanos%2Fas%20en%20el%20establecimiento%20escolar)). In oversubscribed schools, an entrance exam (introduced in 2024) is used to allocate seats among remaining applicants ([www.chaco.gov.ar](https://www.chaco.gov.ar/noticia-ciclo-lectivo-2025-la-preinscripcion-en-nivel-secundario-sera-del-1-al-15-de-octubre-2024-09-29-19-00#:~:text=deben%20brindar%20asesoramiento%20presencial%20a,hermanos%2Fas%20en%20el%20establecimiento%20escolar)). The assignment follows an immediate acceptance (Boston) mechanism: first preferences are processed (with oversubscribed schools selecting students via exam or priority), then unassigned students are considered for their second choice ([www.chaco.gov.ar](https://www.chaco.gov.ar/noticia-ciclo-lectivo-2025-la-preinscripcion-en-nivel-secundario-sera-del-1-al-15-de-octubre-2024-09-29-19-00#:~:text=correspondientes%20al%20orden%20de%20preferencia,tutores%2C%20una%20vez%20que%20haya)). The centralized system was first implemented around 2021 ([www.chaco.gov.ar](https://www.chaco.gov.ar/noticia-ciclo-lectivo-2025-la-preinscripcion-en-nivel-secundario-sera-del-1-al-15-de-octubre-2024-09-29-19-00#:~:text=Por%20cuarto%20a%C3%B1o%20consecutivo%2C%20el,octubre%20del%20corriente%20a%C3%B1o%2C%20seg%C3%BAn)). Prior to 2024, geographic criteria (home address within 1000m or parent’s workplace nearby) were used as additional priorities ([educacion.chaco.gob.ar](https://educacion.chaco.gob.ar/pre-inscripcion-2024/#:~:text=,dentro%20de%20las%20condiciones%20anteriores)), but these were removed in the 2024 reform. Private secondary schools in Resistencia do not participate in the centralized system, handling admissions independently ([www.chaco.gov.ar](https://www.chaco.gov.ar/noticia-ciclo-lectivo-2025-la-preinscripcion-en-nivel-secundario-sera-del-1-al-15-de-octubre-2024-09-29-19-00#:~:text=Por%20otra%20parte%2C%20las%20unidades,de%20Educaci%C3%B3n%20P%C3%BAblica%20de%20Gesti%C3%B3n)).

Resistencia, Argentina does not have a centralized tertiary admission system. Admissions to universities and other tertiary institutions are handled independently by each institution, with no city-wide algorithm or common application process ([chequeado.com](https://chequeado.com/el-explicador/universidad-gratuita-en-argentina-que-pasa-en-uruguay-chile-brasil-bolivia-y-paraguay/#:~:text=En%20la%20Argentina%2C%20el%20acceso,manera%20libre%20e%20irrestricta%20a)). In Argentina, access to public and private higher education is open (ingreso irrestricto) for all students who have completed secondary school ([chequeado.com](https://chequeado.com/el-explicador/universidad-gratuita-en-argentina-que-pasa-en-uruguay-chile-brasil-bolivia-y-paraguay/#:~:text=En%20la%20Argentina%2C%20el%20acceso,manera%20libre%20e%20irrestricta%20a)). Applicants do not rank preferences and there is no centralized matching; each institution sets its own basic admission requirements (e.g. a secondary diploma) and any additional entrance steps (like leveling courses) in line with the national policy of unrestricted access ([www.scielo.org.mx](https://www.scielo.org.mx/article_plus.php?lng=en&pid=S0185-27602023000300104&tlng=es#:~:text=en%20Argentina%2C%20el%20acceso%20a,las%20carreras%20elegidas%20por%20los)). Consequently, no Coordinated Choice and Assignment System exists at the city level for tertiary education, and details such as preference list length, priority criteria, assignment mechanism, adoption year, or reform year are not applicable.

Rosario (Santa Fe province, Argentina) does not have a centralized school choice assignment system for primary education. Admissions are managed by each school based on residency and capacity ([www.unosantafe.com.ar](https://www.unosantafe.com.ar/santa-fe/los-chicos-7-grado-pueden-inscribirse-una-sola-escuela-secundaria-n2048071.html#:~:text=En%20nivel%20inicial%20y%20en,primaria%20articula%20con%20alguna%20escuela)). Children typically attend their local public primary school (determined by home address), and schools must accept all students from their catchment area; only if space remains may they admit students from outside the neighborhood ([www.unosantafe.com.ar](https://www.unosantafe.com.ar/santa-fe/los-chicos-7-grado-pueden-inscribirse-una-sola-escuela-secundaria-n2048071.html#:~:text=En%20nivel%20inicial%20y%20en,primaria%20articula%20con%20alguna%20escuela)). Families do not submit ranked preferences among multiple schools, and there is no single algorithm assigning students to schools ([www.unosantafe.com.ar](https://www.unosantafe.com.ar/santa-fe/los-chicos-7-grado-pueden-inscribirse-una-sola-escuela-secundaria-n2048071.html#:~:text=En%20nivel%20inicial%20y%20en,primaria%20articula%20con%20alguna%20escuela)). If a family fails to secure a spot in a desired out-of-area school, the education authorities ensure the student is offered a place at another school with available seats ([www.unosantafe.com.ar](https://www.unosantafe.com.ar/santa-fe/los-chicos-7-grado-pueden-inscribirse-una-sola-escuela-secundaria-n2048071.html#:~:text=Eso%20implica%20que%20las%20familias,varias%20escuelas%20de%20manera%20simult%C3%A1nea)). Santa Fe’s policy for secondary education includes formal priority criteria (e.g., siblings, staff relatives, feeder school) and random lotteries when applicants exceed capacity ([www.unosantafe.com.ar](https://www.unosantafe.com.ar/santa-fe/los-chicos-7-grado-pueden-inscribirse-una-sola-escuela-secundaria-n2048071.html#:~:text=queremos%20es%20que%20se%20cumpla,la%20norma)); however, at the primary level the key criterion is the student’s residence (school zone) ([www.unosantafe.com.ar](https://www.unosantafe.com.ar/santa-fe/los-chicos-7-grado-pueden-inscribirse-una-sola-escuela-secundaria-n2048071.html#:~:text=En%20nivel%20inicial%20y%20en,primaria%20articula%20con%20alguna%20escuela)). No evidence of a coordinated choice and assignment mechanism for Rosario’s primary schools was found; thus, the system remains uncoordinated, with no specific adoption or reform years to report.

Rosario does not have a centralized school choice system for secondary education. Admissions are handled by each school under Santa Fe province’s regulations ([www.santafe.gob.ar](https://www.santafe.gob.ar/boletinoficial/ver.php?seccion=27-02-2009decreto181-2009.html#:~:text=a,edificio%20de%20la%20Escuela%20Secundaria)) ([www.santafe.gob.ar](https://www.santafe.gob.ar/boletinoficial/ver.php?seccion=27-02-2009decreto181-2009.html#:~:text=En%20caso%20de%20que%20el,el%20procedimiento%20que%20se%20detalla)). Families apply directly to a preferred public secondary school; if applicants exceed available places, the school prioritizes students from an attached primary, children of school staff, and siblings of current students ([www.santafe.gob.ar](https://www.santafe.gob.ar/boletinoficial/ver.php?seccion=27-02-2009decreto181-2009.html#:~:text=a,edificio%20de%20la%20Escuela%20Secundaria)). Any remaining oversubscription is resolved by a public lottery among the applicants in that category ([www.santafe.gob.ar](https://www.santafe.gob.ar/boletinoficial/ver.php?seccion=27-02-2009decreto181-2009.html#:~:text=2,su%20ausencia%20invalidar%C3%A1%20la%20inscripci%C3%B3n)). Entrance exams are not allowed in public secondary admissions ([www.santafe.gob.ar](https://www.santafe.gob.ar/boletinoficial/ver.php?seccion=27-02-2009decreto181-2009.html#:~:text=f,recogidos%20para%20la%20planificaci%C3%B3n%20anual)). Students who do not get a seat through the lottery are guided to other schools with open spots, as regional education authorities publish available vacancies to facilitate placement ([www.santafe.gob.ar](https://www.santafe.gob.ar/boletinoficial/ver.php?seccion=27-02-2009decreto181-2009.html#:~:text=g,en%20las%20cuales%20quedaran%20vacantes)). These procedures apply to public schools only – private secondary schools in Rosario manage their own admissions independently, outside any centralized assignment system ([unr.edu.ar](https://unr.edu.ar/en/la-educacion-en-santa-fe-y-rosario-resultados-aprender-2016/#:~:text=As%20statistical%20information%20has%20advanced%2C,the%20educational%20decisions%20of%20families)).

Rosario does **not** operate a centralized tertiary admission system. Instead, each university or college manages its own admissions. The main public institution, Universidad Nacional de Rosario (UNR), follows Argentina’s tradition of *ingreso irrestricto* (open admission) – any student with a secondary diploma may enroll, with leveling courses offered instead of competitive selection ([www.uncuyo.edu.ar](https://www.uncuyo.edu.ar/prensa/clarin-hay-14-formas-de-acceder-a-la-universidad-estatal#:~:text=universidades%20nacionales%20es%20el%20ingreso,la%20carrera%20con%20m%C3%A1s%20restricciones)). There is no city-wide mechanism for students to rank multiple colleges or receive a single algorithm-generated offer. Applicants must apply directly to each institution/faculty they wish to attend ([unr.edu.ar](https://unr.edu.ar/ingreso-argentinos/#:~:text=El%20tr%C3%A1mite%20de%20preinscripci%C3%B3n%20para,a%20trav%C3%A9s%20del%20sistema%20Guaran%C3%AD)), and can potentially secure multiple admissions. No unified “priority criteria” are used across institutions; the basic requirement is simply completion of high school ([ua3.lat](https://ua3.lat/sistema-de-ingreso-a-la-universidad-en-argentina/#:~:text=Como%20en%20muchos%20otros%20pa%C3%ADses,el%20pa%C3%ADs%20como%20%C2%ABestudios%20secundarios%C2%BB)) (individual programs like Medicine may require an entrance exam as an exception ([www.uncuyo.edu.ar](https://www.uncuyo.edu.ar/prensa/clarin-hay-14-formas-de-acceder-a-la-universidad-estatal#:~:text=universidades%20nacionales%20es%20el%20ingreso,la%20carrera%20con%20m%C3%A1s%20restricciones))). Both public and private tertiary institutions in Rosario handle admissions independently, with public universities being free and open-access and privates setting their own criteria and tuition ([ua3.lat](https://ua3.lat/sistema-de-ingreso-a-la-universidad-en-argentina/#:~:text=La%20admisi%C3%B3n%20sin%20restricciones%20puede,tasa%20para%20iniciar%20los%20estudios)). There has been no implementation of a coordinated choice/assignment system in Rosario to date, so no adoption or reform year is applicable.

Primary school admissions in San Carlos de Bariloche (Río Negro province) are managed through a centralized process. Families list up to three preferred public primary schools ([rionegro.gov.ar](https://rionegro.gov.ar/articulo/51283/siguen-las-inscripciones-de-estudiantes-para-sala-de-4-1-grado-y-1-ano#:~:text=En%20este%20marco%2C%20es%20de,Educaci%C3%B3n%20Secundaria%20se%20eligen%20ocho)), and a provincial algorithm assigns each student a single seat based on stated preferences and established priority criteria (e.g. siblings at the school and local residence) ([rionegro.gov.ar](https://rionegro.gov.ar/articulo/51106/inician-las-inscripciones-de-estudiantes-a-sala-de-4-1-grado-y-1-ano#:~:text=Adem%C3%A1s%2C%20detall%C3%B3%20que%20para%20esto,vacantes%20que%20tenga%20cada%20escuela%E2%80%9D)) ([educacion.rionegro.gov.ar](https://educacion.rionegro.gov.ar/inscripcionestudiantes#:~:text=El%20sistema%20de%20inscripci%C3%B3n%20tiene,para%20acceder%20a%20una%20vacante)). If a school has more applicants than spots, a public lottery is held to allocate places fairly ([rionegro.gov.ar](https://rionegro.gov.ar/articulo/51106/inician-las-inscripciones-de-estudiantes-a-sala-de-4-1-grado-y-1-ano#:~:text=llamamos%20clasificaci%C3%B3n%20y%20sorteos%2C%20en,vacantes%20que%20tenga%20cada%20escuela%E2%80%9D)). This coordinated system guarantees every child a place in a public primary school ([rionegro.gov.ar](https://rionegro.gov.ar/articulo/51106/inician-las-inscripciones-de-estudiantes-a-sala-de-4-1-grado-y-1-ano#:~:text=El%20procedimiento%20permite%20garantizar%20una,Cr%C3%A9dito%3A%20Gobierno%20de%20R%C3%ADo%20Negro)). The framework was introduced via provincial resolutions in 2017 ([educacion.rionegro.gov.ar](https://educacion.rionegro.gov.ar/inscripcionestudiantes#:~:text=Los%20criterios%20de%20ingreso%20directo,prioridad%20estip%C3%BAlado%20por%20las%20Resoluciones)), with a standardized pre-registration and lottery procedure implemented in 2021 ([educacion.rionegro.gov.ar](https://educacion.rionegro.gov.ar/inscripcionestudiantes#:~:text=edilicia%20de%20la%20instituci%C3%B3n)). Private schools in Bariloche do not use this centralized assignment system, handling admissions independently.

San Carlos de Bariloche (Province of Río Negro) uses a centralized school choice system for public secondary education. Families submit a ranked list of up to 8 preferred public secondary schools ([rionegro.gov.ar](https://rionegro.gov.ar/articulo/51283/siguen-las-inscripciones-de-estudiantes-para-sala-de-4-1-grado-y-1-ano#:~:text=En%20este%20marco%2C%20es%20de,Educaci%C3%B3n%20Secundaria%20se%20eligen%20ocho)).
